A couple of notes:<br>
<br>
*) Most wizards I've seen in the Grey content themselves with just a couple of mobs. It's not that they can't handle more, it's that the spawn pattern and all the annoying traps make it difficult to get four mobs all in one place without getting unwanted adds. Wizards are particularly frustrated by those worms which can't be snared or rooted. I think a wizard would rather fight off a rockfiend than a worm.<br>
<br>
*) Two mobs gave my 57 earth pet(s) quite the beating. I'm not sure if more mobs would be worth the hassle of even trying to round up. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unanid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nanid</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.scorpz.com/icq.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#333333>(7/22/02 8:58:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=228.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.scorpz.com/nanidezz.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: IR soloing ideas</span><hr size=1> Pointless.... i'll prefer normal one on one with these mobs.... my mana basically stays and only having to break a bit after few pulls.... and not to mention.. a lot safer even if you go LD or having suddenspike lag which kills us most of the time.<br>
